---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
---

<Layout title="Jan Piotrowski - Privacy Policy">
    <main class="legal">
        <Navbar />

        <article class="content">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 5, 2026</p>

            <section>
                <h2>Introduction</h2>
                <p>
                    This Privacy Policy explains how Laus Code, registered in
                    the Netherlands ("we", "us", "our"), collects, uses, and
                    protects your personal data when you use our services. This
                    policy applies to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>jan.wf</strong> &mdash; our website</li>
                    <li><strong><a href="https://portal.semig.dev">Authentik</a></strong> &mdash; our identity and authentication service</li>
                    <li><strong><a href="https://wyjazdy.top67.pl">TREK</a></strong> &mdash; our trip tracking application</li>
                    <li><strong><a href="https://git.semig.dev">Forgejo</a></strong> &mdash; our self-hosted Git forge</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    We process personal data in accordance with the General Data
                    Protection Regulation (GDPR) and applicable Dutch data
                    protection legislation.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Data Controller</h2>
                <p>
                    The data controller for all services is Laus Code, registered
                    in the Netherlands. For questions regarding data processing,
                    you can contact us at
                    <a href="mailto:jan@lauscode.com">jan@lauscode.com</a>.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
                <h3>jan.wf (Website)</h3>
                <p>
                    Our website does not collect personal information from
                    visitors. There are no user accounts, forms, or tracking
                    scripts on this site.
                </p>

                <h3>Authentik</h3>
                <p>
                    When you use our Authentik identity service, we collect:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Account credentials (username, email address, password hash)</li>
                    <li>Authentication logs (login times, IP addresses, device information)</li>
                    <li>Session data required for single sign-on functionality</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>TREK</h3>
                <p>
                    When you use TREK, we collect:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Trip data you provide (destinations, dates, notes)</li>
                    <li>Account information linked through Authentik</li>
                    <li>Usage data necessary for the functioning of the application</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Forgejo</h3>
                <p>
                    When you use our Forgejo instance, we collect:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Account information linked through Authentik</li>
                    <li>Repository data and content you upload (code, issues, comments)</li>
                    <li>Git activity metadata (commits, pushes, pull requests)</li>
                    <li>Usage data necessary for the functioning of the service</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
                <p>
                    We process your personal data on the following legal grounds
                    under Article 6 of the GDPR:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Contract performance</strong> &mdash; processing necessary to provide the services you signed up for (Authentik, TREK)</li>
                    <li><strong>Legitimate interest</strong> &mdash; server logs and security monitoring to protect our infrastructure</li>
                    <li><strong>Consent</strong> &mdash; where applicable, for optional data processing activities</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Server Logs</h2>
                <p>
                    All our services may automatically log standard technical
                    information such as your IP address, browser type, referring
                    page, and the date and time of your visit. These logs are
                    used solely for maintaining the security and performance of
                    the server and are not shared with third parties.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    Our website (jan.wf) does not use cookies. Authentik and
                    TREK use strictly necessary cookies for session management
                    and authentication. These are functional cookies required for
                    the services to operate and do not require consent under
                    GDPR.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Data Retention</h2>
                <p>
                    We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary
                    to provide our services or as required by law. Server logs
                    are retained for a limited period for security purposes.
                    Account data is retained for the duration of your use of the
                    services and deleted upon account deletion.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>
                    We do not sell, trade, or otherwise share your personal data
                    with third parties. We do not embed third-party analytics,
                    advertising, or social media tracking services in any of our
                    services.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Your Rights</h2>
                <p>
                    Under the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your
                    personal data:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right of access</strong> &mdash; request a copy of the data we hold about you</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> &mdash; request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> &mdash; request deletion of your data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to restriction</strong> &mdash; request limitation of processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> &mdash; receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to object</strong> &mdash; object to processing based on legitimate interest</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
                    <a href="mailto:jan@lauscode.com">jan@lauscode.com</a>. We will respond
                    to your request within 30 days. You also have the right to
                    lodge a complaint with the Dutch Data Protection Authority
                    (Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens).
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Data Security</h2>
                <p>
                    We take appropriate technical and organisational measures to
                    protect your personal data against unauthorised access,
                    alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>External Links</h2>
                <p>
                    Our services may contain links to external sites. We are not
                    responsible for the privacy practices or content of those
                    sites.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
                <p>
                    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any
                    changes will be reflected on this page with an updated date.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h2>Contact</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can
                    reach us at <a href="mailto:jan@lauscode.com">jan@lauscode.com</a>.
                </p>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    :global(body) {
        font-family:
            system-ui,
            -apple-system,
            Segoe UI,
            Roboto,
            Helvetica,
            Arial,
            sans-serif;
        background: #f8f9fb;
        color: #111827;
    }

    .legal {
        min-height: 100vh;
    }

    .content {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
    }

    .content h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .last-updated {
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: #6b7280;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .content h2 {
        font-size: 1.75rem;
        margin-top: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #e5e7eb;
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .content p {
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: #4b5563;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        text-align: justify;
    }

    .content h3 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        color: #111827;
    }

    .content ul {
        padding-left: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 1.125rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
    }

    .content a {
        color: #111827;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
        transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
    }

    .content a:hover {
        border-bottom-color: currentColor;
    }
</style>
